Absolutely! When it comes to using developer tools for tweaking CSS variables, especially with an eye toward responsive design and accessibility, consider the following steps:

1. Define CSS Custom Properties: Start by defining a series of CSS custom properties (variables) at the root level so that they can be easily managed and reused across different components. For example:
   • :root {
       --primary-color: #3498db;
       --secondary-color: #9b59b6;
       --accent-color: #e74c3c; /* consider replacing with a friendly color for accessibility */
       …
    }

2. Choose Accessible Color Codes: When substituting colors, use tools like Adobe Color, Accessible Color Palette, or Contrast Checkers to ensure that your new colors meet accessibility guidelines. For your issue with red-green differences, adjust --accent-color by choosing hues that are distinguishable under various conditions (say, using shades of blue or purple).

3. Implement Media Queries for Responsiveness: In your CSS, implement media queries that adjust these variables on different screen sizes. This could look like:
   • @media (max-width: 768px) {
       :root {
         --primary-color: #2980b9;
         --secondary-color: #8e44ad;
         --accent-color: #c0392b;
       }
     }
   The goal here is to ensure that your theme remains accessible and visually balanced on smaller screens where lighting and contrast can vary.

4. Utilize Developer Tools for Live Editing: Modern browsers like Chrome and Firefox come equipped with robust developer tools that allow you to tweak CSS variables in real-time. This live editing can help you dynamically see how changes in your color variables affect the entire interface, making it easier to find the best accessible palette.

5. Test and Iterate: Always preview your changes under various conditions (different devices, ambient lighting conditions) using the developer tool’s device simulation features. This iterative process is invaluable in fine-tuning both the aesthetic and accessible aspects of your themes.

This approach gives you granular control over the visual presentation while ensuring that your design remains accessible across various devices and settings. Feel free to dive deeper and experiment with these tools to perfectly tailor your digital interface.
